During the course the following topcs will be discussed:
Concepts and survey methods of pharmacoepidemiology and pharmacoeconomics; random clinical studies; drug consumption in Estoni; principles of biostatistical analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce concepts and study methods of pharmacoepidemiology and pharmacoeconomics. To learn critical evaluation of scientific publications in described fields and practice study methods in pharmacoeconomics and use of medicines. To introduce the principles of clinical studies of medicines.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - to be aware of concepts of pharmacoepidemiology, pharmacoeconomics and clinical studies of medicines;  - to find and evaluate information concerning above described disciplines;  - capable to systematize and if required implement into practice acquired knowledge and skills; - capable to use IT to find required information
